(17, 1, '2024-03-29 06:18:32', '2024-03-29 06:18:32', 'Kuari Pass Winter Trek\nWelcome to Buddy hikers winter treks - the beginning of unforgettable trails.\nLocated in the depths of Garhwal Himalayas and nestled on the western rim of Nanda Devi Biosphere Reserve is Kuari Pass, the only trekkable mountain pass in the winters with its summit located at an altitude of 12500 ft. Kuari Pass trek is one of the most sought after treks in the winter season. A trek that enchants any mountain lover with its mesmerising views of the mighty Himalayan Mountain peaks, thick, dense and ancient forests with their healing energies, and exotic wildlife interactions along the trail. Whether you are a beginner getting comfortable with the cold breeze of the mountains or a pro looking to explore the depths of your limits, Kuari Pass has something to offer to everyone.\nAnd to top it off, you will be led and guided by a team of elite SF veterans from the Indian Armed Forces. An opportunity to learn from battle hardened adventurers and walk shoulder to shoulder with them, to explore your limits, and your true potential.\nTrek Details\nAltitude - 12500 ft\nBase camp - Tugashi village, Joshimath, Uttarakhand\nDifficulty - Easy to Moderate\nBatch - Max 15 persons\nItinerary\nDay 1 - Arrival at Buddy Hikers (Tugashi Village, Joshimath)\nHow to reach -\nParticipants must arrive at Rishikesh by 07 am.\nNearest Airport - Jolly Grant - 30 mins to Rishikesh\nNearest Railway station - Rishikesh Railway station\nNearest Bus stop - Rishikesh ISBT\nPickup point for trekkers - Natraj Chowk\nRishikesh to Tugashi village is a 266 km journey by road. It takes approximately 09 hrs to reach Tugashi base camp. Participants will travel by either a Tempo traveller which costs Rs 13000/vehicle or 5-6 seaters which costs Rs 9999/vehicle. Transport will be arranged at sharp 09 am from Rishikesh.\nDay 1: 09 am - Departure from Rishikesh\n07 pm - Arrival at Tugashi base camp\n07 pm to 09 pm - Meet &amp; Greet + Di